reviewText: My children love the Backyardigans, and so do I!  Each show is full of singing, problem solving and friendship, wonderful for preschoolers.  This set has the following four episodes (the first one is the only Christmas episode):*The Action Elves Save Christmas Eve - Abominable Snowmen Tyrone and Austin accidentally take Santa's magic sack.  Now the action elves (Uniqua, Pablo and Tasha) must use their talents to bring the sack back to Santa and save Christmas.*Pablor and the Acorns - Acorn scouts Tasha, Tyrone and Austin are in a space race for the Crystal of Power vs. the evil space-dictators Pablor and Uniquor!*The Big Dipper Diner - Space police Tyrone and Tasha mistake Uniqua and Pablo's sweetest customer as a dangerous space alien known as the Blarg.*The Amazing Splashinis - Uniqua, Tyrone and Pablo, diving experts, are practicing their newest, highest, most riskiest dive at the Splashini Water Park when a sea monster interupts their practice.  While he's great fun to play with, they need to get down to business!Each of the four episodes is what you come to expect from the Backyardigans - just plain cute!

reviewText: The Christmas one is very pro-Santa.  The celebrity voice is lost on anyone who hasn't read who it is. You cannot hear his voice.  The others are good or bad depending on your like or dislike of the characters.  However, The Amazing Splashinis misses a number of teachable moments. Uniqua, Tyrone and Pablo are very mean to the sea-serpent and instead of apologizing when they realize that they need him, they just make him help them. And never say thank you.  Overall, typical Backyardigan stories but wish there were more than just the four episodes and more extras for the adults.
summary: Christmas and more with the Backyardigans

reviewText: Bought this for my little grandbunny (20 months old)  who loves these guys. I thought it was just a Christmas show (I'm sure it said otherwise in the description, I honestly didn't bother to read it). It has her favorite episode (and others) which is the Big Dipper Diner that I really hadn't been able to locate as a stand alone DVD. These little guys keep her very entertained on the long ride home.
